gomodel:SYNGO_1171  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: In this paper, the presence of the VGAT in different parts of the brain was shown by EM (Fig. 10). Furthermore, using EM and two EM analysis method, it was shown that VGAT is a synaptic vesicle protein (Fig. 11). The two analysis method were, first: the correlation of the presence of immunogold particles and synaptic vesicles within squares placed in a lattice over the terminals, and the second: the intercenter distance between immunogold particles and synaptic vesicles that was highly significantly different from that between vesicles and points randomly distributed over the terminals (Fig.12).\n\n22/11/2017 Pim\n- Based on the known transmembrane topology of the protein, the \"integral component of ... membrane\" term was chosen.. Experimental description: Nine adult rats (Wistar strain; Moellegaard Hansen) of 150-200 gm were deeply anesthetized with pentobarbital (100 mg/kg), the right atrium was cut open, and the animals were perfused through the left ventricle-aorta." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0030285 replaced by GO:0030672" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-1542-3498" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-3898-5197" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-0808-7003" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_1171" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

